    "created_at": "2018-01-21T13:38:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-01-21T13:53:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This and the common \"attack order turns into a move order\" complaints are caused by https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/5f54e46eae98632e3f38d5fc13287789a32e3735/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Activities/Move/MoveAdjacentTo.cs#L86-L95\r\n\r\nWhen the target is lost under fog this code will swap out the move order without letting it finish.  The unit then starts the next move order from the center of the cell that it never finished moving to, causing the jump.\r\n\r\nThe proper fix here is to cancel the inner activity and then when that has completed naturally end the `MoveAdjacentTo` ( / `MoveWithinRange`).  It should be the responsibility of the parent activity to handle when the target was lost part way."
